article.headline: Delaware 97, Penn 94
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Jawan Carter scored a career-high 35 points and Delaware eked out its first win of the season with a 97-94 double-overtime victory over Penn on Saturday night. Carter made a school-record 19 free throws for the Blue Hens (1-2) -- breaking the record of 18 -- though he missed seven foul shots in the game. Delaware was 11-for-20 from the line in overtime while Penn was 5-for-14. Alphonso Dawson added 28 points for the Blue Hens. The Quakers (0-3) led 50-40 at halftime and 67-52 with 11:50 left in regulation. The Blue Hens tied the game at 80 with 44 seconds left on a D.J. Boney 3-pointer. Zack Rosen's layup put Penn ahead 82-80, then Hakim McCullar's tip-in at the buzzer forced overtime. Penn missed shots as time expired in both overtimes, with Malcolm Washington's 3 bouncing off the backboard in the second OT. Rosen led Penn with a career-high 25 points.
